---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="About Tobias Treppmann and the missional product design framework."
>
  <div class="container">
    <section class="section">
      <h1>About</h1>

      <div class="section mt-xl">
        <h2>Tobias Treppmann</h2>

        <p>
          Tobias Treppmann is a product designer, theologian, and the founder of
          <a href="https://oratio.co" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Oratio.co</a>. He is currently pursuing
          an M.A. in Leadership at Kairos University while building
          <a href="https://aperto.bible" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Aperto</a>, a digital spiritual
          formation platform.
        </p>

        <p>
          The missional product design framework emerged from his research paper <em>Digital Spiritual Formation: The
          Aperto Vision</em> (2026), which draws on 195+ sources across theology, behavioral science, and product design.
        </p>

        <p>
          His work sits at the intersection of three worlds: the ancient Christian tradition of spiritual formation, the
          emerging field of digital theology, and the practical discipline of product design. He is interested in how
          digital tools can serve human flourishing without exploiting attention, agency, or community.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: var(--spacing-2xl);">Connect</h3>

        <p>
          This framework is published openly as a resource for the field. If you're building technology for spiritual
          formation — or human flourishing more broadly — I'd love to hear from you.
        </p>

        <div style="margin-top: var(--spacing-lg);">
          <p>
            <strong>Email:</strong>
            <a href="mailto:hello@treppmann.design">hello@treppmann.design</a>
          </p>
        </div>

        <h3 style="margin-top: var(--spacing-2xl);">Elsewhere</h3>

        <ul style="list-style: none; padding: 0;">
          <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);">
            <a href="https://oratio.co" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Oratio.co</a> — Design for spiritual
            direction
          </li>
          <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);">
            <a href="https://aperto.bible" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Aperto.bible</a> — A digital
            spiritual formation platform
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <section class="section-alt mt-2xl" style="margin-left: -1rem; margin-right: -1rem; padding: var(--spacing-2xl) var(--spacing-lg);">
        <div class="container">
          <h2>About This Site</h2>

          <p>
            This site presents the complete missional product design framework — a set of nine principles and six
            diagnostic questions for building technology that serves spiritual formation and human flourishing.
          </p>

          <p>
            The framework is the result of research into how digital tools can support formation without exploiting
            engagement, how to serve community while honoring the individual spiritual journey, and how to design for
            grace instead of guilt.
          </p>

          <p>
            If you're building digital tools for spiritual formation, a church community, or any technology intended to
            serve human flourishing, these principles are offered openly as a resource and starting point for your own
            discernment.
          </p>

          <p style="margin-top: var(--spacing-xl);">
            <a href="/" class="btn">Explore the Framework</a>
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  h3 {
    color: var(--color-primary);
  }

  ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
  }

  li {
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
    color: var(--color-text-light);
  }

  li a {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  li a:hover {
    color: var(--color-accent-light);
  }
</style>
